New things in version 1.1.2:

Fixed:
Many instances there the CPU got stuck

New:
There are new versual feedback then chaining (this is an extreme help)
Vs. Mode for single player with 7 difficulties
"make install" now works
"make remove" added, it removes everything installed by "make install"
There is an icon in xpm format

Changed:
New graphics for garbage blocks
Screenshots are now saved to ~/.gamesaves/blockattack/screenshots on UNIX systems
Combos give a little more points

Bugs (all known bugs):
If you have solved a puzzle and restart it by pushing "Push", then fail it you will still see "Winner"
If a puzzle file is extended the new puzzles will appear solved (it has always been like that)
Windows 9x compatibility is broken, I don't know why. It shouldn't happen!
There is a possible bufferoverflow if your home dictory "~/" has an extremly long path, ie if the whole path get to more than 254 charecters
The menu is not always redrawed correctly
